abdominal wall muscles","Pericardial cavity lining","Pleural membranes","Central tendon of the diaphragm and portion of the liver"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecentral tendon of the diaphragm and portion of the liver\u003C/strong\u003E develop from the septum transversum, which is a thick mesodermal plate that forms during the fourth week of embryological development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior abdominal wall muscles\u003C/strong\u003E develop from the lateral plate mesoderm and somites\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecostal cartilages of the thorax\u003C/strong\u003E develop from the lateral plate mesoderm\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Epericardial cavity lining\u003C/strong\u003E develops from the lateral plate mesoderm splanchnic layer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Epleural membranes\u003C/strong\u003E develop from the lateral plate mesoderm\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe septum transversum initially forms as a partial partition between the thoracic and abdominal cavities, eventually contributing to both the diaphragm\u0027s central tendon and hepatic tissue.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The septum transversum develops into the central tendon of the diaphragm and a portion of the liver during embryological development.","The septum transversum is a mesodermal structure that forms during the fourth week of development."],"references":["Gaillard R, Steegers EA, de Jongste JC, Hofman A, Jaddoe VW. Tracking of fetal growth characteristics during different trimesters and the risks of adverse birth outcomes. Int J Epidemiol. 2014 Aug;43(4):1140-53. doi: 10.1093/ije/dyu036. Epu